headline: Freeport-McMoRan (NYSE:FCX) Climbs 13% As Copper Demand Surges
summary: Freeport-McMoRan (NYSE:FCX) saw its stock price rise by 13% over the past week, a significant move amid a broader market that remained mostly stable. This increase comes against a backdrop of mixed performances in major indexes, with the S&P 500 and Nasdaq Composite both experiencing declines. Although no single event conclusively explains Freeport's price surge, the volatility in the tech-heavy Nasdaq, driven by declines in mega-cap stocks like Tesla and Nvidia, may have redirected attention...
